Khosla’s Sunborne, Suryachakra Plan Solar Plant in India

-- B y   N a t a l i e   O b i k o   P e a r s o n
-- 
2011-06-15T08:29:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-15/khosla-s-sunborne-suryachakra-plan-solar-plant-in-india.html
Sunborne Energy Technologies, a
solar power developer backed by  India  billionaire Vinod Khosla,
and Suryachakra Power Corp. plan to set up a 5-megawatt sun-
powered plant in the south Asian nation.  The project, which will use concentrated solar technology,
will be built in eastern Andhra Pradesh state in India,
Suryachakra said in a statement to the Bombay Stock Exchange.  Suryachakra plans to sell elecricity produced at the plant
to the state’s Central Power Distribution Company under a power
purchase agreement, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Natalie Obiko Pearson in Mumbai at 
 npearson7@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at   landberg@bloomberg.net . 